    "body": "# Pull Request\n\n## Description\nThis PR introduces a comprehensive routing structure to the application using `react-router-dom` and `HelmetProvider` for improved navigation and SEO.\n\nKey changes include:\n- **New Routing:** Implemented a full application shell with `Header` and `Footer` components, and defined routes for various pages including `Home`, `Services`, `Solutions`, `Resources`, `Support`, `Pricing`, `Marketplace`, `Sitemap`, `About`, and `Contact`.\n- **Detailed Service Pages:** Added dedicated, content-rich pages for:\n    - **AI Services:** Featuring RAG chatbots, IDP, predictive analytics, computer vision, and MLOps, complete with pricing packages and capabilities.\n    - **Micro SaaS:** Showcasing niche SaaS products like email deliverability, sales copilot, local SEO booster, and edge AI inference, with subscription-based pricing.\n    - **IT Services:** Covering cloud migration, DevOps/SRE, and Zero Trust security, including service descriptions and pricing ranges.\n- **SEO Enhancements:** Integrated `react-helmet-async` to manage document head tags (titles, meta descriptions, canonical links) for better search engine visibility on new pages.\n- **Temporary Home Page:** A lightweight `HomeLite` page was introduced and set as the default route to facilitate the build process and bypass potential conflicts with existing `Home.tsx` components.\n\nThese changes aim to diversify service offerings, provide detailed information to users, and improve overall site structure and discoverability.\n\n## Type of Change\n- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)\n- [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)\n- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to not work as expected)\n- [x] Documentation update (SEO meta tags)\n- [x] Refactoring (no functional changes)\n- [ ] Performance improvement\n- [ ] Security fix\n\n## Testing\n- [ ] I have tested this change locally\n- [ ] I have added tests for this change\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] I have tested the build process\n\n## Checklist\n- [ ] My code follows the project's style guidelines\n- [ ] I have performed a self-review of my code\n- [ ] I have commented my code, particularly in hard-to-understand areas\n- [x] I have made corresponding changes to the documentation (SEO meta tags)\n- [ ] My changes generate no new warnings\n- [ ] I have added tests that prove my fix is effective or that my feature works\n- [ ] New and existing unit tests pass locally with my changes\n- [ ] Any dependent changes have been merged and published\n\n## Screenshots (if applicable)\nN/A\n\n## Additional Notes\nThe `HomeLite` page is a temporary measure to enable the build. Further work is needed to properly integrate or replace the original `Home.tsx` and `HomeOptimized.tsx` components. The build process was initiated in the background and its status is pending. Any remaining merge conflict remnants will be addressed in subsequent steps.\n\n---\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/background-agent?bcId=bc-e520d83d-efeb-47b9-8863-af89b194629b\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-dark.svg\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-light.svg\"><img alt=\"Open in Cursor\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor.svg\"></picture></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://cursor.com/agents?id=bc-e520d83d-efeb-47b9-8863-af89b194629b\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-dark.svg\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-light.svg\"><img alt=\"Open in Web\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web.svg\"></picture></a>\n\n",
